		<p><span class = "title">About Us: </span>McAlpine Tankersley Architecture is the partnership of Bobby McAlpine
and Greg Tankersley.   Both are natives of Alabama and graduates of
Auburn University.  Their practice, celebrating its twentieth
anniversary, attracts clients from all over the United States and
Europe.  Described as &#8220;nurturing, compassionate, soulful,&#8221; the firm's
architecture, wedding historical precedence with graceful modern living,
is a timeless and romantic pursuit of “The Inheritable House”.</p>

<p><img src="office_new.jpg" alt="McAline Tankersley Offices" border="0" width="213" height="350" align="left" vspace="4" hspace="4">It is this approach which as led their work and that of their innovative design team to be featured in SOUTHERN ACCENTS, HOUSE
BEAUTIFUL, VERANDA, ARTS &amp; ANTIQUES, SOUTHERN LIVING, HOUSE AND GARDEN,
METROPOLITAN HOME and on HGTV.  McAlpine Tankersley Architecture
continues to be recognized by its peers as recipients of Product Design
Awards, the Southern Home Award and Award of Merit Honor Awards given by
the American Institute of Architects.</p>

<p>Mr. McAlpine divides his time between McAlpine Tankersley and <a href="http://www.mcalpineboothferrier.com"">McAlpine
Booth &amp; Ferrier Interiors</a>, an interior design firm he began in 1997.  An
award-winning furniture designer, his latest creations are included in a
furniture line called <a href="http://www.mcalpinehome.com">McAlpine Home</a> and is manufactured by <a href="http://www.leeindustries.com">Lee Industries</a> in North Carolina.</p>

<p>Mr. Tankersley has been active in civic concerns in Montgomery including
serving as President of the Garden District Preservation Association,
the historic district where he has renovated an Italianate villa.  Greg
and his wife, Mary Robin Jurkiewicz, have one child, Marian Sullivan
Tankersley.</p></td></tr></table></div></td></tr></table>
